Definition: a legislative act finding a person guilty of treason or felony without a trial
Example: bills of attainder are prohibited by the Constitution of the United States
Synonyms: bill, noun, group, law, c, a, legislative, act, finding, person, guilty, of, treason, or, felony, without, trial, bills, attainder, are, prohibited, by, the, Constitution, United, States
Category: noun.communication
